**Output Location**: `/home/barista/agentic_barista/runs/synthesize/logincontext/run_4/logincontext/LoginContextRefinements.java`

Here is the final specification:

```java
package logincontext;

import javax.security.auth.Subject;
import javax.security.auth.callback.CallbackHandler;
import javax.security.auth.login.Configuration;
import liquidjava.specification.ExternalRefinementsFor;
import liquidjava.specification.StateRefinement;
import liquidjava.specification.StateSet;

@ExternalRefinementsFor("javax.security.auth.login.LoginContext")
@StateSet({"authenticated", "created", "loggedout"})
public interface LoginContextRefinements {

    @StateRefinement(to = "created(this)")
    public void LoginContext(String name);

    @StateRefinement(to = "created(this)")
    public void LoginContext(String name, Subject subject);

    @StateRefinement(to = "created(this)")
    public void LoginContext(String name, CallbackHandler callbackHandler);

    @StateRefinement(to = "created(this)")
    public void LoginContext(String name, Subject subject, CallbackHandler callbackHandler);

    @StateRefinement(to = "created(this)")
    public void LoginContext(String name, Subject subject, CallbackHandler callbackHandler, Configuration config);

    @StateRefinement(from = "created(this)", to = "authenticated(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "authenticated(this)")
    public void login();

    @StateRefinement(from = "authenticated(this)", to = "loggedout(this)")
    public void logout();

    public Subject getSubject();

}
```

**Design decisions and rationale:**

1. **No `@Refinement` value annotations**: All constructor and method parameters are object types (`String`, `Subject`, `CallbackHandler`, `Configuration`) — none are `int` or `double`. LiquidJava `@Refinement` predicates only apply to numeric types, so no value refinements are applicable.

2. **`getSubject()` added**: The generated template omitted this method. The Mermaid shows it as a self-loop in all three states (Created, Authenticated, LoggedOut), so it has no `from` (callable from any state) and no `to` (no state transition). Return type is `Subject` (object), so no `@Refinement` on the return.

3. **`login()` dual `@StateRefinement`**: Correctly captures two distinct transitions — from `Created` (leading to `Authenticated`) and from `Authenticated` (self-loop, no `to` needed).

4. **`logout()` restricted to `Authenticated`**: The `from = "authenticated(this)"` constraint ensures logout cannot be called from `Created` or `LoggedOut`, matching the Mermaid exactly.

5. **Imports**: Added `javax.security.auth.Subject`, `javax.security.auth.callback.CallbackHandler`, and `javax.security.auth.login.Configuration` for the parameter types to compile correctly.

